praveśayasva māṁ nātha mahāmokṣapuraṁ varamiti ||
tvaṁ me ... varam iti Nāgabodhi's Viṁśatividhi 7.3–4: tvaṁ me śāstā mahārata | icchāmy ahaṁ mahānātha bodhisattvanayaṁ dr̥ḍhaṁ | dehi me samayaṁ tattvaṁ bodhicittaṁ ca dehi me || buddhaṁ dharmaṁ ca saṅghaṁ ca dehi me śaraṇatrayaṁ | praveśayasva māṁ nātha mahāmokṣapuraṁ varam iti || CHECK TANAKA'S ED!!; Durgatipariśodhana: tataḥ śiṣyān praveśayet. tatra pañcaśikṣāpadaparigr̥hītena śrāmaṇerakabhikṣusaṁvaragr̥hītena vā ācāryābhiṣekārhe nācāryapādayoḥ praṇipatyaivaṁ vaktavyam. tvaṁ me śāstā mahārataḥ | icchāmy ahaṁ mahānātha mahābodhinayaṁ dr̥ḍham | dehi me samayatattvaṁ saṁvaraṁ ca dadasva me || iti. (p.284)\ In later texts, the first pāda is embedded into a single stanza. See, e.g., VA \S\ 20.4: mr̥tyujanmajarānakramakarādibhyānakāt | bhavābdher eka uddhartā tvaṁ me śāstā mahārataḥ || icchāmy ahaṁ mahānātha mahābodhinayaṁ dr̥ḍham | dehi me samayaṁ tattvaṁ bodhicittaṁ ca dehi me || buddhaṁ dharmaṁ ca saṅghaṁ ca dehi me śaraṇatrayam | praveśayasva māṁ nātha mahāmokṣapuraṁ varam || iti pāṭhayan ... (p.375)
